# Gemini API Configuration
# Choose ONE of the following options:

# Option 1: Google Cloud Service Account (Vertex AI) - For enterprise use
# Format: Single-line JSON with all service account fields
# GEMINI_CREDS={"type":"service_account","project_id":"your-project","private_key_id":"xxx","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_KEY\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n","client_email":"xxx@xxx.iam.gserviceaccount.com","client_id":"xxx","auth_uri":"https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth","token_uri":"https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token","auth_provider_x509_cert_url":"https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/certs","client_x509_cert_url":"xxx","universe_domain":"googleapis.com"}

# Option 2: API Key in JSON format - For simple deployment
# Format: GEMINI_CREDS={"api_key":"your_api_key_here"}
# GEMINI_CREDS={"api_key":"AIzaSyXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX"}

# Option 3: Direct API Key (fallback) - Simplest method
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSyXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# IMPORTANT:
# - Uncomment and fill ONE option in your .env or .env.local file
# - For service account: Must be single-line JSON (no line breaks)
# - See SERVICE_ACCOUNT_SETUP.md for detailed service account setup
# - See GEMINI_CREDS_SETUP.md for API key setup

